This ORM part is written with Django frame.
You could use the following command to remove the database built by the basic operations before:
     python3 manage.py flush
You need to change the ALLOWED_HOST according to your virtual machine address in orm/settings.
Then you can run the program by the following command:
     python3 manage.py runserver 0:8000
Turn to the address localhost:8000, you need to click on Load Data first, to create objects according to the four given files, then you can start query.
The results will be output on the command terminal.
